        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3418584385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6836676354931747418">Azazeel by Youssef Ziedan <br/>Narrator is an anonymous translator who is translating the writings of a fifth century&apos;s Egyptian monk and physician called Hypa. <br/>Hypa&apos;s journey between churches and monasteries reveal how much religious extremism was spread and what extent the conflicts explode between Christian, Jews and Pagans. Also, how religion expliots for personal agendas.<br/>Ziedan beautifully form the dialogues between Azazeel and Hypa and also the internal psychological conflict.</span>
  <span id="freeText6836676354931747418" style="display:none">Azazeel by Youssef Ziedan <br />Narrator is an anonymous translator who is translating the writings of a fifth century's Egyptian monk and physician called Hypa. <br />Hypa's journey between churches and monasteries reveal how much religious extremism was spread and what extent the conflicts explode between Christian, Jews and Pagans. Also, how religion expliots for personal agendas.<br />Ziedan beautifully form the dialogues between Azazeel and Hypa and also the internal psychological conflict.</span>
